HEADWORD: Souter
<hw>Sou"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>s<?/t<?/re</ets>, fr. It. <ets>sutor</ets>, fr. <ets>suere</ets> to
sew.]</ety> <def>A shoemaker; a cobbler.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no work better than another to please God: . . . to wash
dishes, to be a <qex>souter</qex>, or an apostle, -- all is one.</q>
<rj><qau>Tyndale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

